text: Replaced the faulty PSU and rerouted the cabling; server booted normally afterward with no further power drops observed during a 2hour burn-in test.
label: positive

text: User reported slow logins but I couldnt reproduce the issue. Checked AD, GPOs, and network latency; all within normal range. Might be intermittent, will need monitoring tools to confirm.
label: neutral

text: Patch deployment went smoothly on all 14 machines except one laptop that kept timing out. After a manual install and reboot, the patch applied successfully.
label: positive

text: Ticket lacked essential details (no hostname, no screenshots, no error codes). Had to call the user twice to understand the problem, which delayed the resolution.
label: negative

text: Cleaned a large amount of dust from the desktop and reseated the RAM. The random restarts stopped immediately. System passed extended memory diagnostics.
label: positive

text: VPN client keeps disconnecting every 1015 minutes, but only for users on the 3rd floor WiFi. Strongly suspect an access point or DHCP lease issue rather than endpoint configuration.
label: neutral

text: User insisted their monitor was broken, but it was just set to HDMI2 with nothing connected. Switched it back to DisplayPort and everything worked fine.
label: positive

text: Replaced a swollen laptop battery. Old battery was at 23% health and causing sudden shutdowns. New battery passed calibration and holds charge properly.
label: positive

text: Could not complete the OS re-image because the network boot environment was down. PXE server not responding; had to postpone and log this as a dependency.
label: negative

text: Configured the new label printer with the correct driver and template. Test prints aligned perfectly and the warehouse staff confirmed its working as expected.
label: positive

text: Users profile was corrupted after a forced shutdown. Created a new profile and migrated data; login time dropped from 7 minutes to under 40 seconds.
label: positive

text: The replacement SSD arrived without the mounting bracket, so I couldnt fully install it in the rack server. Temporarily secured it but we need the proper caddy ASAP.
label: negative

text: Network drops reported in conference room B were due to a damaged patch cable under the floor box. Replaced cable and the connection stabilized immediately.
label: positive

text: Spent over an hour tracking down a license key issue that could have been avoided if procurement had updated the asset record. Documentation is still lagging behind reality.
label: negative

text: Upgraded BIOS and firmware on 6 laptops without any complications. Verified BitLocker status before and after; no recovery prompts were triggered.
label: positive

text: Could not replicate the reported printing issue. Printer logs show no errors, and test pages from multiple users printed fine. Asked user to reopen with a screenshot if it happens again.
label: neutral

text: User appreciated that I walked them through the new MFA app instead of just sending a link. Enrollment completed successfully on both phone and tablet.
label: positive

text: Found that the root cause of the recurring account lockouts was a password saved on an old iPad. Removed the profile and the lockouts stopped.
label: positive

text: Ticket was misrouted to desktop support even though it clearly involved a database permission issue. Had to reassign it to the DB team after basic checks.
label: negative

text: Installed the requested software but the user didnt have the necessary license tier to access the advanced features they wanted. Advised them to contact their manager for approval.
label: neutral

text: Replaced the broken keyboard on the warehouse PC. Several keys were physically missing. New keyboard tested OK and user signed off the job.
label: positive

text: WiFi coverage in the far corner of the office is still weak even after repositioning the AP. We likely need an additional access point installed there.
label: negative

text: Removed multiple adware programs and browser extensions from the users PC. After cleanup, CPU usage dropped from 90% idle to around 10%.
label: positive

text: Couldnt complete the onsite visit because security hadnt been informed. Spent 30 minutes at reception waiting for clearance. This should be coordinated better.
label: negative

text: Helped the finance team with a shared mailbox issue. Recreated the Outlook profile and reattached the mailbox; all historical emails re-synced correctly.
label: positive

text: Users webcam problem was due to privacy shutter being closed, not a driver issue. Showed them how to check it next time to avoid unnecessary tickets.
label: positive

text: Server room temperature sensor kept sending false alerts because the probe was touching the exhaust of a backup UPS. Moved it to a neutral area and alerts stopped.
label: positive

text: Imaging station froze twice during deployment. Logs suggest a storage performance issue on the deployment server, not with the client device.
label: neutral

text: User was frustrated because their ticket had been open for 5 days with no update. The delay was caused by pending vendor confirmation that no one followed up on.
label: negative

text: Repaired a frayed power cable on a monitor and labeled it for replacement. Its safe for now, but this should be swapped out within the week.
label: neutral

text: Configured a static IP for the network printer as requested by IT management. Updated DNS records and verified printing from three different VLANs.
label: positive

text: Couldnt join the new laptop to the domain because we hit the machine account quota for that OU. Notified the AD team to clean up stale objects.
label: neutral

text: Helped a remote user with a failing USBC dock. Firmware update fixed the intermittent display issues without needing a replacement dock.
label: positive

text: The floor map in the ticket system is outdated, which made it hard to locate the users desk. Had to call them again for directions.
label: negative

text: Ran full SMART diagnostics on the users HDD and found multiple reallocated sectors. Backed up the data and requested a drive replacement.
label: neutral

text: The new barcode scanner integrated with the inventory system without any special drivers. Just had to configure the prefix and suffix for the fields.
label: positive

text: User claimed they lost access to their shared drive, but permissions had not changed. Their drive letter mapping was overwritten by a USB device. Remapped successfully.
label: positive

text: Tried to assist with a thirdparty app issue, but its completely unsupported and undocumented. Had to direct the user back to the vendor.
label: negative

text: Restored a deleted folder from last nights backup within 10 minutes. User was relieved because it contained a month of project work.
label: positive
